# OmniRadon workspace — environment example
#
# This workspace repo does not have its own runtime environment.
# Each service manages its own .env file inside its own directory.
#
# Relevant .env files per service:
#   gateway/.env          ← copy from gateway/.env.example (needs TASKS_SERVICE_TOKEN, TASKS_*_URL)
#   auth-service/.env     ← copy from auth-service/.env.example
#   task-manager/apps/task-manager-api/.env  ← copy from .env.example (GATEWAY_SERVICE_TOKEN = gateway TASKS_SERVICE_TOKEN)
#   llm-service/.env      ← copy from llm-service/.env.example (DATABASE_URL, NATS_URL, OLLAMA_BASE_URL)
#
# shell, diary, and settings web apps do not require manual .env for local dev beyond gateway tokens.
